explanation: The solution uses a backtracking approach to explore all possible combinations of dividing the array into k subsets. It calculates the target sum for each subset and iterates through the array, adding elements to subsets until the target sum is reached or all elements are used. The backtracking mechanism allows for exploring different combinations and pruning the search space when a subset cannot be formed.

